comments.body:
> Still help wanted here.

@spolom We don't control anything about the version of Dapr that Microsoft opts to host in their Azure Container Apps solution. If you're having an issue with Dapr as presented through ACA, you need to take that up with Microsoft Support as we can't do anything about it.

As you noted - locally it works fine. We control the runtime that runs there, so I'm happy to hear that works. But we can't do anything about what bits ACA is loading nor how it's presented there.
